The paper discusses a machine-learning model (decision-tree ensemble model) and proposes a method for formally verifying it and detecting input value ranges that lead to failures. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of reliability in systems, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for detecting failures, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
